forms.name: Wobbuffet
forms.entry: It hates light and shock. If attacked, it inflates its body to pump up its counterstrike.

forms.name: Girafarig
forms.entry: Its tail, which also contains a small brain, may bite on its own if it notices an alluring smell.

forms.name: Pineco
forms.entry: It hangs and waits for flying insect prey to come near. It does not move about much on its own.

forms.name: Forretress
forms.entry: Its entire body is shielded by a steel-hard shell. What lurks inside the armor is a total mystery.

forms.name: Dunsparce
forms.entry: When spotted, this Pokémon escapes backward by furiously boring into the ground with its tail.

forms.name: Gligar
forms.entry: It builds its nest on a steep cliff. When it is done gliding, it hops along the ground back to its nest.

forms.name: Steelix
forms.entry: Its body has been compressed deep under the ground. As a result, it is even harder than a diamond.

forms.name: Snubbull
forms.entry: Although it looks frightening, it is actually kind and affectionate. It is very popular among women.

forms.name: Granbull
forms.entry: It is actually timid and easily spooked. If attacked, it flails about to fend off its attacker.

forms.name: Qwilfish
forms.entry: It shoots the poison spines on its body in all directions. Its round form makes it a poor swimmer.

forms.name: Qwilfish
forms.entry: Fishers detest this troublesome Pokémon because it sprays poison from its spines, getting it everywhere. A different form of Qwilfish lives in other regions.

forms.name: Scizor
forms.entry: Its wings are not used for flying. They are flapped at high speed to adjust its body temperature.

forms.name: Shuckle
forms.entry: The fluid secreted by its toes carves holes in rocks for nesting and can be mixed with Berries to make a drink.

forms.name: Heracross
forms.entry: This powerful Pokémon thrusts its prized horn under its enemies' bellies then lifts and throws them.

forms.name: Sneasel
forms.entry: Vicious in nature, it drives Pidgey from their nests and feasts on the eggs that are left behind.

forms.name: Sneasel
forms.entry: Its sturdy, curved claws are ideal for traversing precipitous cliffs. From the tips of these claws drips a venom that infiltrates the nerves of any prey caught in Sneasel's grasp.

forms.name: Teddiursa
forms.entry: If it finds honey, its crescent mark glows. It always licks its paws because they are soaked with honey.

forms.name: Ursaring
forms.entry: Although it is a good climber, it prefers to snap trees with its forelegs and eat fallen Berries.

forms.name: Slugma
forms.entry: It never sleeps. It has to keep moving because if it stopped, its magma body would cool and harden.

forms.name: Magcargo
forms.entry: The shell on its back is just skin that has cooled and hardened. It breaks easily with a slight touch.

forms.name: Swinub
forms.entry: It rubs its snout on the ground to find and dig up food. It sometimes discovers hot springs.

forms.name: Piloswine
forms.entry: Because the long hair all over its body obscures its sight, it just keeps charging repeatedly.

forms.name: Corsola
forms.entry: The points on its head absorb nutrients from clean water. They cannot survive in polluted water.

forms.name: Corsola
forms.entry: Watch your step when wandering areas oceans once covered. What looks like a stone could be this Pokémon, and it will curse you if you kick it.

forms.name: Remoraid
forms.entry: Using its dorsal fin as a suction pad, it clings to a Mantine's underside to scavenge for leftovers.

forms.name: Octillery
forms.entry: It instinctively sneaks into rocky holes. If it gets sleepy, it steals the nest of a fellow Octillery.

forms.name: Delibird
forms.entry: It always carries its food with it, wherever it goes. If attacked, it throws its food at the opponent.

forms.name: Mantine
forms.entry: As it majestically swims, it doesn't care if Remoraid attach to it for scavenging its leftovers.

forms.name: Skarmory
forms.entry: Its sturdy wings look heavy, but they are actually hollow and light, allowing it to fly freely in the sky.

forms.name: Houndour
forms.entry: It uses different kinds of cries for communicating with others of its kind and for pursuing its prey.

forms.name: Houndoom
forms.entry: If you are burned by the flames it shoots from its mouth, the pain will never go away.

forms.name: Kingdra
forms.entry: It is said that it usually hides in underwater caves. It can create whirlpools by yawning.

forms.name: Phanpy
forms.entry: As a sign of affection, it bumps with its snout. However, it is so strong, it may send you flying.

forms.name: Porygon2
forms.entry: This upgraded version of Porygon is designed for space exploration. It can't fly, though.

forms.name: Stantler
forms.entry: Those who stare at its antlers will gradually lose control of their senses and be unable to stand.

forms.name: Smeargle
forms.entry: A special fluid oozes from the tip of its tail. It paints the fluid everywhere to mark its territory.

forms.name: Tyrogue
forms.entry: It is always bursting with energy. To make itself stronger, it keeps on fighting even if it loses.

forms.name: Hitmontop
forms.entry: If you become enchanted by its smooth, elegant, dance-like kicks, you may get drilled hard.

forms.name: Smoochum
forms.entry: Its lips are the most sensitive parts on its body. It always uses its lips first to examine things.

forms.name: Elekid
forms.entry: It rotates its arms to generate electricity, but it tires easily, so it charges up only a little bit.

forms.name: Magby
forms.entry: Each and every time it inhales and exhales, hot embers dribble out of its mouth and nostrils.

forms.name: Miltank
forms.entry: Its milk is packed with nutrition, making it the ultimate beverage for the sick or weary.

forms.name: Blissey
forms.entry: Anyone who takes even one bite of Blissey's egg becomes unfailingly caring and pleasant to everyone.

forms.name: Raikou
forms.entry: The rain clouds it carries let it fire thunderbolts at will. They say that it descended with lightning.

forms.name: Entei
forms.entry: Volcanoes erupt when it barks. Unable to restrain its extreme power, it races headlong around the land.

forms.name: Suicune
forms.entry: Said to be the reincarnation of north winds, it can instantly purify filthy, murky water.

forms.name: Larvitar
forms.entry: It feeds on soil. After it has eaten a large mountain, it will fall asleep so it can grow.

forms.name: Pupitar
forms.entry: Its shell is as hard as sheet rock, and it is also very strong. Its Thrashing can topple a mountain.

forms.name: Tyranitar
forms.entry: Extremely strong, it can change the landscape. It has an insolent nature that makes it not care about others.

forms.name: Lugia
forms.entry: It is said to be the guardian of the seas. It is rumored to have been seen on the night of a storm.

forms.name: Ho-Oh
forms.entry: Legends claim this Pokémon flies the world's skies continuously on its magnificent seven-colored wings.

forms.name: Celebi
forms.entry: This Pokémon wanders across time. Grass and trees flourish in the forests in which it has appeared.

forms.name: Treecko
forms.entry: The soles of its feet are covered by countless tiny spikes, enabling it to walk on walls and ceilings.

forms.name: Grovyle
forms.entry: The leaves growing out of Grovyle's body are convenient for camouflaging it from enemies in the forest. This Pokémon is a master at climbing trees in jungles.

forms.name: Sceptile
forms.entry: The leaves that grow on its arms can slice down thick trees. It is without peer in jungle combat.

forms.name: Torchic
forms.entry: It has a flame sac inside its belly that perpetually burns. It feels warm if it is hugged.

forms.name: Combusken
forms.entry: It lashes out with 10 kicks per second. Its strong fighting instinct compels it to keep up its offensive until the opponent gives up.

forms.name: Blaziken
forms.entry: It learns martial arts that use punches and kicks. Every several years, its old feathers burn off, and new, supple feathers grow back in their place.

forms.name: Mudkip
forms.entry: Extremely strong, it can change the landscape. It has an insolent nature that makes it not care about others.

forms.name: Marshtomp
forms.entry: Its toughened hind legs enable it to stand upright. Because it weakens if its skin dries out, it replenishes fluids by playing in mud.

forms.name: Swampert
forms.entry: Extremely strong, it can change the landscape. It has an insolent nature that makes it not care about others.

forms.name: Poochyena
forms.entry: It savagely threatens foes with bared fangs. It chases after fleeing targets tenaciously. It turns tail and runs, however, if the foe strikes back.

forms.name: Mightyena
forms.entry: It will always obey the commands of a skilled trainer. Its behavior arises from its living in packs in ancient times.

forms.name: Zigzagoon
forms.entry: A Pokémon with abundant curiosity. It shows an interest in everything, so it always zigs and zags.

forms.name: Zigzagoon
forms.entry: Its restlessness has it constantly running around. If it sees another Pokémon, it will purposely run into them in order to start a fight.

forms.name: Linoone
forms.entry: It charges prey at speeds over 60 mph. However, because it can only run straight, it often fails.

forms.name: Linoone
forms.entry: It uses its long tongue to taunt opponents. Once the opposition is enraged, this Pokémon hurls itself at the opponent, tackling them forcefully.

forms.name: Wurmple
forms.entry: It loves to eat leaves. If it is attacked by a Starly, it will defend itself with its spiked rear.

forms.name: Silcoon
forms.entry: It conserves its energy by moving as little as possible. It awaits evolution while drinking only a little rainwater.

forms.name: Beautifly
forms.entry: Despite its appearance, it has an aggressive nature. It attacks by jabbing with its long, thin mouth.

forms.name: Cascoon
forms.entry: Its body, which is made of soft silk, hardens over time. When cracks appear, evolution is near.

forms.name: Dustox
forms.entry: A nocturnal Pokémon. Drawn by streetlights, they messily eat the leaves of trees lining boulevards.

forms.name: Lotad
forms.entry: This Pokémon lives in ponds with clean water. It is known to ferry small Pokémon across ponds by carrying them on the broad leaf on its head.

forms.name: Lombre
forms.entry: Lombre's entire body is covered by a slippery, slimy film. It feels horribly unpleasant to be touched by this Pokémon's hands. Lombre is often mistaken for a human child.

forms.name: Ludicolo
forms.entry: When it hears festive music, all the cells in its body become stimulated, and it begins moving in rhythm. It does not quail even when it faces a tough opponent.

forms.name: Seedot
forms.entry: If it remains still, it becomes impossible to distinguish from real nuts. It delights in surprising foraging Pidgey.

forms.name: Nuzleaf
forms.entry: They live in holes bored in large trees. The sound of its grass flute fills listeners with dread.

forms.name: Shiftry
forms.entry: A Pokémon that was feared as a forest guardian. It can read the foe's mind and take preemptive action.

forms.name: Taillow
forms.entry: Although it is small, it is very courageous. It will take on a larger Skarmory on an equal footing. However, its will weakens if it becomes hungry.

forms.name: Swellow
forms.entry: If its two tail feathers are standing at attention, it is proof of good health. It soars elegantly in the sky.

forms.name: Wingull
forms.entry: It makes its nest on a sheer cliff at the edge of the sea. It has trouble keeping its wings flapping in flight. Instead, it soars on updrafts.

forms.name: Pelipper
forms.entry: It is a flying transporter that carries small Pokémon in its beak. It bobs on the waves to rest its wings.

forms.name: Ralts
forms.entry: It uses the horns on its head to sense human emotions. It is said to appear in front of cheerful people.

forms.name: Kirlia
forms.entry: If its Trainer becomes happy, it overflows with energy, dancing joyously while spinning about.

forms.name: Gardevoir
forms.entry: It apparently does not feel the pull of gravity because it supports itself with psychic power. It will give its life to protect its trainer.

forms.name: Surskit
forms.entry: They usually live on ponds, but after an evening shower, they may appear on puddles in towns.

forms.name: Masquerain
forms.entry: It intimidates foes with the large eyelike patterns on its antennae. Because it can't fly if its wings get wet, it shelters itself from rain under large trees and eaves.

forms.name: Shroomish
forms.entry: It prefers damp places. By day it remains still in the forest shade. It releases toxic powder from its head.

forms.name: Breloom
forms.entry: Its short arms stretch when it throws punches. Its technique is equal to that of pro boxers.

forms.name: Slakoth
forms.entry: It sleeps virtually all day and night long. It doesn't change its nest its entire life, but it sometimes travels great distances by swimming in rivers.

forms.name: Vigoroth
forms.entry: It can't keep still because its blood boils with energy. It runs through the fields and mountains all day to calm itself. If it doesn't, it can't sleep at night.

forms.name: Slaking
forms.entry: Slaking spends all day lying down and lolling about. It eats grass growing within its reach. If it eats all the grass it can reach, this Pokémon reluctantly moves to another spot.

forms.name: Nincada
forms.entry: Because it lived almost entirely underground, it is nearly blind. It uses its antennae instead.

forms.name: Ninjask
forms.entry: Because it darts about vigorously at high speed, it is very difficult to see. Hearing its distinctive cries for too long induces a headache.

forms.name: Shedinja
forms.entry: A discarded bug shell that came to life. Peering into the crack on its back is said to steal one's spirit.

forms.name: Whismur
forms.entry: Usually, its cries are like quiet murmurs. If frightened, it shrieks at the same volume as a jet plane.

forms.name: Loudred
forms.entry: When it stamps its feet and bellows, it generates ultrasonic waves that can blow apart a house.

forms.name: Exploud
forms.entry: It has sound-generating organs all over its body. It communicates with others by adjusting the tone and volume of the cries it emits.

forms.name: Makuhita
forms.entry: It toughens up by slamming into thick trees over and over. It gains a sturdy body and dauntless spirit.

forms.name: Hariyama
forms.entry: It has the habit of challenging others without hesitation to tests of strength. It's been known to stand on train tracks and stop trains using forearm thrusts.

forms.name: Azurill
forms.entry: Its tail, which is packed with nutrition, is very bouncy like a rubber ball. On sunny days they gather at the edge of water and splash about for fun.

forms.name: Nosepass
forms.entry: Its nose is a magnet. As a result, this Pokémon always keeps its face pointing north.

forms.name: Skitty
forms.entry: It is said to be difficult to earn its trust. However, it is extremely popular for its cute looks and behaviour.

forms.name: Delcatty
forms.entry: It dislikes dirty places. It often searches for a comfortable place in which to groom itself.

forms.name: Sableye
forms.entry: It hides in the darkness of caves. Its diet of gems has transformed its eyes into gemstones.

forms.name: Mawile
forms.entry: Its giant jaws are actually steel horns that transformed. It fools foes into complacency with its adorable gestures, then chomps them with its huge jaws.

forms.name: Aron
forms.entry: It usually lives deep in mountains. However, hunger may drive it to eat railroad tracks and cars.

forms.name: Lairon
forms.entry: It habitually shows off its strength with the size of sparks it creates by ramming its steel body into boulders.

forms.name: Aggron
forms.entry: It claims a large mountain as its sole territory. It mercilessly thrashes those that violate its space.

forms.name: Meditite
forms.entry: It continually meditates for hours every day. As a result of rigorous and dedicated yoga training, it has tempered its spiritual power so much it can fly.

forms.name: Medicham
forms.entry: Through crushingly harsh yoga training, it gained the power to foretell its foe's actions. It battles with elegant, dance-like movement.

forms.name: Electrike
forms.entry: It generates electricity using friction from the atmosphere. In seasons with especially arid air, its entire body blazes with violent showers of sparks.

forms.name: Manectric
forms.entry: It discharges electricity from its mane. It creates a thundercloud overhead to drop lightning bolts.

forms.name: Plusle
forms.entry: It cheers on partners while scattering sparks from its body. It climbs telephone poles to absorb electricity.

forms.name: Minun
forms.entry: Its dislike of water makes it take shelter under the eaves of houses in rain. It uses pom-poms made of sparks for cheering.

forms.name: Volbeat
forms.entry: It lives around clean ponds. At night, its rear lights up. It converses with others by flashing its light.

forms.name: Illumise
forms.entry: It guides Volbeat to draw signs in night skies. There are scientists that study the patterns it creates.

forms.name: Roselia
forms.entry: Its flowers give off a relaxing fragrance. The stronger its aroma, the healthier the Roselia is.

forms.name: Gulpin
forms.entry: There is nothing its stomach can't digest. While it is digesting, vile, overpowering gases are expelled.

forms.name: Swalot
forms.entry: It gulps anything that fits in its mouth. Its special enzymes can dissolve anything.

forms.name: Carvanha
forms.entry: They swarm any foe that invades their territory. Their sharp fangs can tear out boat hulls.

forms.name: Sharpedo
forms.entry: The ruffian of the seas, it has fangs that crunch through iron. It swims by jetting water from its rear.

forms.name: Wailmer
forms.entry: When it sucks in a large volume of seawater, it becomes like a big, bouncy ball. It eats a ton of food daily.

forms.name: Wailord
forms.entry: It is among the largest of all Pokémon. It herds prey in a pack then swallows the massed prey in one gulp.

forms.name: Numel
forms.entry: Numel is extremely dull witted - it doesn't notice being hit. However, it can't stand hunger for even a second. This Pokémon's body is a seething cauldron of boiling magma.

forms.name: Camerupt
forms.entry: If angered, the humps on its back erupt in a shower of molten lava. It lives in the craters of volcanoes.

forms.name: Torkoal
forms.entry: It burns coal inside its shell. If it is attacked, it belches thick, black smoke and flees.

forms.name: Spoink
forms.entry: It apparently dies if it stops bouncing about. It carries a pearl from Clamperl on its head.

forms.name: Grumpig
forms.entry: It can gain control over foes by doing odd dance steps. The black pearls on its forehead are precious gems.

forms.name: Spinda
forms.entry: No two Spinda are said to have identical patterns. It confuses foes with its stumbling motions.

forms.name: Trapinch
forms.entry: Its big jaws crunch through boulders. Because its head is so big, it has a hard time getting back upright if it tips over onto its back.

forms.name: Vibrava
forms.entry: It generates ultrasonic waves by violently flapping its wings. After making its prey faint, it melts the prey with acid.

forms.name: Flygon
forms.entry: Flygon is nicknamed "the elemental spirit of the desert." Because its flapping wings whip up a cloud of sand, this Pokémon is always enveloped in a sandstorm while flying.

forms.name: Cacnea
forms.entry: The more arid and harsh the environment, the more pretty and fragrant a flower Cacnea grows. This Pokémon battles by wildly swinging its thorny arms.

forms.name: Cacturne
forms.entry: After spending thousands of years in harsh deserts, its blood transformed into the same substances as sand. It is nocturnal, so it hunts at night.

forms.name: Swablu
forms.entry: Its wings are like cotton tufts. If it perches on someone's head, it looks like a cotton hat.

forms.name: Altaria
forms.entry: It hums in a beautiful soprano voice. It flies among white clouds in the blue sky. It launches intensely hot fireballs from its mouth.

forms.name: Zangoose
forms.entry: If it comes across a Seviper, its fur bristles and it assumes its battle pose. Its sharp claws are its best weapon.

forms.name: Seviper
forms.entry: Seviper and Zangoose are eternal rivals. It counters a Zangoose's dazzling agility with its swordlike tail, which also oozes a horrible poison.

forms.name: Lunatone
forms.entry: Lunatone was discovered at a location where a meteorite fell. As a result, some people theorize that this Pokémon came from space. However, no one has been able to prove this theory so far.

forms.name: Solrock
forms.entry: Solrock is a new species of Pokémon that is said to have fallen from space. It floats in air and moves silently. In battle, this Pokémon releases intensely bright light.

forms.name: Barboach
forms.entry: It probes muddy riverbeds with its two long whiskers. A slimy film protects its body.

forms.name: Whiscash
forms.entry: Mysteriously, it can foretell earthquakes. In the daytime, it sleeps in mud at the bottom of a pond. When it awakens, it continually feeds throughout the night.

forms.name: Corphish
forms.entry: Once it grips prey with its large pincers, it will never let go, no matter what. It is a hardy Pokémon that can thrive in any environment.

forms.name: Crawdaunt
forms.entry: A brutish Pokémon that loves to battle. It will crash itself into any foe that approaches its nest.

forms.name: Baltoy
forms.entry: It was discovered in ancient ruins. While moving, it constantly spins. It stands on one foot even when asleep.

forms.name: Claydol
forms.entry: Claydol is an enigma that appeared from a clay statue made by an ancient civilization dating back 20,000 years. This Pokémon shoots beams from both its hands.

forms.name: Lileep
forms.entry: It became extinct roughly 100 million years ago. It was regenerated from a fossil using advanced techniques.

forms.name: Cradily
forms.entry: It drags its heavy body along the seafloor. It makes its nest in the shallows of warm seas. Cradily can be seen on beaches when the tide goes out.

forms.name: Anorith
forms.entry: It is a kind of Pokémon progenitor. It uses its extending claws to catch prey hiding among rocks on the seafloor.

forms.name: Armaldo
forms.entry: Protected by a hard shell, its body is very sturdy. It skewers prey with its claws to feed.

forms.name: Feebas
forms.entry: Ridiculed for its shabby appearance, it is ignored by researchers. It lives in ponds choked with weeds.

forms.name: Milotic
forms.entry: Milotic is breathtakingly beautiful. Those that see it are said to forget their combative spirits.

forms.name: Castform
forms.entry: It alters its form depending on the weather. Changes in the climate such as the temperature and humidity appear to affect its cellular structure.

forms.name: Castform
forms.entry: This is the form Castform takes on the brightest of days. Its skin is unexpectedly hot to the touch, so approach with care.

forms.name: Castform
forms.entry: This is the form Castform takes when soaked with rain. When its body is compressed, water will seep out as if from a sponge.

forms.name: Castform
forms.entry: This is the form Castform takes when hit by hail. In an experiment where it was placed in a freezer, it didn't change to this form.

forms.name: Kecleon
forms.entry: It can freely change its body's color. The zigzag pattern on its belly doesn't change, however.

forms.name: Shuppet
forms.entry: It loves to feed on feelings like envy and malice. Its upright horn catches the emotions of people.

forms.name: Banette
forms.entry: Strong feelings of hatred turned a puppet into a Pokémon. If it opens its mouth, its cursed energy escapes.

forms.name: Duskull
forms.entry: Duskull wanders lost among the deep darkness of midnight. There is an oft-told admonishment given to misbehaving children that this Pokémon will spirit away bad children who earn scoldings from their mothers.

forms.name: Dusclops
forms.entry: It is thought that its body is hollow with only a spectral ball of fire burning inside. However, no one has been able to confirm this theory as fact.

forms.name: Tropius
forms.entry: It flies by flapping its broad leaves. The bunch of fruit that grows around its neck is deliciously sweet. In the spring, it scatters pollen from its neck.

forms.name: Chimecho
forms.entry: They fly about very actively when the hot season arrives. They communicate among themselves using seven different and distinguishing cries.

forms.name: Absol
forms.entry: It appears when it senses an impending natural disaster. As a result, it was mistaken as a doom-bringer.

forms.name: Wynaut
forms.entry: Wynaut gather on moonlit nights to play by squeezing up against each other. By being squeezed, this Pokémon gains endurance and is trained to dole out powerful counterattacks.

forms.name: Snorunt
forms.entry: Snorunt survives by eating only snow and ice. Old folklore claims that a house visited by this Pokémon is sure to prosper for many generations to come.

forms.name: Glalie
forms.entry: It has a body of ice that won't melt, even with fire. It can instantly freeze moisture in the atmosphere.

forms.name: Spheal
forms.entry: It rolls across ice floes to reach shore because its body is poorly shaped for swimming.

forms.name: Sealeo
forms.entry: It touches new things with its nose to test for smell and feel. It plays by spinning Spheal on its nose.

forms.name: Walrein
forms.entry: It shatters ice with its big tusks. Its thick blubber repels not only the cold, but also enemy attacks.

forms.name: Clamperl
forms.entry: It makes a single pearl during its lifetime. The pearl is said to amplify psychic power.

forms.name: Huntail
forms.entry: To withstand the crushing pressure of water deep under the sea, its spine is very thick and sturdy. Its tail, which is shaped like a small fish, has eyes that light up.

forms.name: Gorebyss
forms.entry: Its swimming form is exquisitely elegant. With its thin mouth, it feeds on seaweed that grows between rocks.

forms.name: Relicanth
forms.entry: It has remained unchanged for 100 million years. It was discovered during a deep-sea exploration.

forms.name: Luvdisc
forms.entry: During the spawning season, countless Luvdisc congregate at coral reefs, turning the waters pink.

forms.name: Bagon
forms.entry: Dreaming of one day flying, it practices by leaping off cliffs every day.

forms.name: Shelgon
forms.entry: It hardly eats while it awaits evolution. It becomes hardier by enduring hunger. Its shell peels off the instant it begins to evolve.

forms.name: Salamence
forms.entry: Salamence came about as a result of a strong, long-held dream of growing wings. It is said that this powerful desire triggered a sudden mutation in this Pokémon's cells, causing it to sprout its magnificent wings.

forms.name: Beldum
forms.entry: When Beldum gather in a swarm, they move in perfect unison as if they were but one Pokémon. They communicate with each other using brain waves.

forms.name: Metang
forms.entry: It floats midair using magnetism. Its body is so tough, even a crash with a jet plane won't leave a scratch.

forms.name: Metagross
forms.entry: Metagross has four brains in total. Combined, the four brains can breeze through difficult calculations faster than a supercomputer. This Pokémon can float in the air by tucking in its four legs.

forms.name: Regirock
forms.entry: It is entirely composed of rocks with no sign of a brain or heart. It is a mystery even to modern scientists.

forms.name: Regice
forms.entry: Its entire body is made of Antarctic ice. After extensive studies, researchers believe the ice was formed during an ice age.

forms.name: Registeel
forms.entry: Its body is harder than any other kind of metal. The body metal is composed of a mysterious substance. Not only is it hard, it shrinks and stretches flexibly.

forms.name: Latias
forms.entry: Latias is highly intelligent and capable of understanding human speech. It is covered with a glass-like down. The Pokémon enfolds its body with its down and refracts light to alter its appearance.

forms.name: Latios
forms.entry: Latios will only open its heart to a trainer with a compassionate spirit. This Pokémon can fly faster than a jet plane by folding its forelegs to minimize air resistance.

forms.name: Kyogre
forms.entry: Kyogre is named in mythology as the Pokémon that expanded the sea by covering the land with torrential rains and towering tidal waves. It took to sleep after a cataclysmic battle with Groudon.

forms.name: Groudon
forms.entry: Groudon has long been described in mythology as the Pokémon that raised lands and expanded continents. This Pokémon took to sleep after a cataclysmic battle with Kyogre.

forms.name: Rayquaza
forms.entry: Rayquaza is said to have lived for hundreds of millions of years in the earth's ozone layer, above the clouds. Its existence had been completely unknown because it lived so high in the sky.

forms.name: Jirachi
forms.entry: Jirachi will awaken from its sleep of a thousand years if you sing to it in a voice of purity. It is said to make true any wish that people desire.

forms.name: Deoxys
forms.entry: Deoxys emerged from a virus that came from space. It is highly intelligent and wields psychokinetic powers. This Pokémon shoots lasers from the crystalline organ on its chest.

forms.name: Deoxys
forms.entry: This Deoxys has transformed into its aggressive guise. It can fool enemies by altering its appearance.

forms.name: Deoxys
forms.entry: When it changes form, an aurora appears. It absorbs attacks by altering its cellular structure.

forms.name: Deoxys
forms.entry: A Pokémon that mutated from an extraterrestrial virus exposed to a laser beam. Its body is configured for superior agility and speed.

forms.name: Turtwig
forms.entry: Made from soil, the shell on its back hardens when it drinks water. It lives along lakes.

forms.name: Grotle
forms.entry: It knows where pure water wells up. It carries fellow Pokémon there on its back.

forms.name: Torterra
forms.entry: Some Pokémon are born on a Torterra's back and spend their entire life there.

forms.name: Chimchar
forms.entry: It is very agile. Before going to sleep, it extinguishes the flame on its tail to prevent fires.

forms.name: Monferno
forms.entry: A bigger fire on its tail and a brighter blue pattern on its face means its rank in its pack is higher.

forms.name: Infernape
forms.entry: Its crown of fire is indicative of its fiery nature. It is beaten by none in terms of quickness.

forms.name: Piplup
forms.entry: A poor walker, it often falls down. However, its strong pride makes it puff up its chest without a care.

forms.name: Prinplup
forms.entry: It lives alone, away from others. Apparently, every one of them believes it is the most important.

forms.name: Empoleon
forms.entry: The three horns that extend from its beak attest to its power. The leader has the biggest horns.

forms.name: Starly
forms.entry: Because they are weak individually, they form groups. However, they bicker if the group grows too big.

forms.name: Staravia
forms.entry: They maintain huge flocks, although fierce scuffles break out between various flocks.

forms.name: Staraptor
forms.entry: It never stops attacking even if it is injured. It fusses over the shape of its comb.

forms.name: Bidoof
forms.entry: With nerves of steel, nothing can perturb it. It is more agile and active than it appears.

forms.name: Bibarel
forms.entry: A river dammed by Bibarel will never overflow its banks, which is appreciated by people nearby.

forms.name: Kricketot
forms.entry: Its legs are short. Whenever it stumbles, its stiff antennae clack with a xylophone-like sound.

forms.name: Kricketune
forms.entry: It crosses its knifelike arms in front of its chest when it cries. It can compose melodies ad lib.

forms.name: Shinx
forms.entry: The extension and contraction of its muscles generates electricity. It glows when in trouble.

forms.name: Luxio
forms.entry: Strong electricity courses through the tips of its sharp claws. A light scratch causes fainting in foes.

forms.name: Luxray
forms.entry: When its eyes gleam gold, it can spot hiding prey—even those taking shelter behind a wall.

forms.name: Budew
forms.entry: Sensitive to changing temperature, the bud is said to bloom when it feels the sun's warm touch.

forms.name: Roserade
forms.entry: With the movements of a dancer, it strikes with whips that are densely lined with poison thorns.

forms.name: Cranidos
forms.entry: A lifelong jungle dweller from 100 million years ago, it would snap obstructing trees with head butts.

forms.name: Rampardos
forms.entry: Its skull is as hard as iron. It is a brute that tears down jungle trees while catching prey.

forms.name: Shieldon
forms.entry: It habitually polishes its face by rubbing it against tree trunks. It is weak to attacks from behind.

forms.name: Bastiodon
forms.entry: When they lined up side by side, no foe could break through. They shielded their young in that way.

forms.name: Burmy
forms.entry: To shelter itself from cold, wintry winds, it covers itself with a cloak made of twigs and leaves.

forms.name: Burmy
forms.entry: It creates a cloak by weaving together sand, mud, and silk it has spat out. This earthen cloak is ruined by wind and rain, so the Pokémon hides away in caves and other such places.

forms.name: Burmy
forms.entry: When confronted by a lack of other materials, Burmy will create its cloak using dust and refuse. The cloak seems to be more comfortable than one would think.

forms.name: Wormadam
forms.entry: When Burmy evolves, its cloak becomes a part of its body. Wormadam's cloak is never shed.

forms.name: Wormadam
forms.entry: Its earthen skin is reasonably hard—it has no problem repelling a Starly's pecking, at least.

forms.name: Wormadam
forms.entry: Its body, composed of refuse, blends in to the scenery so much as to be inconspicuous. This seems to be the perfect way for the Pokémon to evade the detection of predators.

forms.name: Mothim
forms.entry: It loves the honey of flowers and steals honey collected by Combee.

forms.name: Combee
forms.entry: At night, Combee sleep in a group of about a thousand, packed closely together in a lump.

forms.name: Vespiquen
forms.entry: Its abdomen is a honeycomb for grubs. It raises its grubs on honey collected by Combee.

forms.name: Pachirisu
forms.entry: A pair may be seen rubbing their cheek pouches together in an effort to share stored electricity.

forms.name: Buizel
forms.entry: It has a flotation sac that is like an inflatable collar. It floats on water with its head out.

forms.name: Floatzel
forms.entry: It floats using its well-developed flotation sac. It assists in the rescues of drowning people.

forms.name: Cherubi
forms.entry: The small ball holds the nutrients needed for evolution. Apparently, it is very sweet and tasty.

forms.name: Cherrim
forms.entry: As a bud, it barely moves. It sits still, placidly waiting for sunlight to appear.

forms.name: Cherrim
forms.entry: Cheerfully active on sunny days. Immediately closes its petals and becomes immobile once the sun becomes hidden, however.

forms.name: Shellos
forms.entry: For the most part, it makes its home along the seashore. Its color and form differ according to its habitat and the quality of its food.

forms.name: Shellos
forms.entry: Shellos lives in the sea and feasts on plankton. The lovelier the ocean where Shellos resides, the more vibrant its color becomes.

forms.name: Gastrodon
forms.entry: It has strong regenerative capabilities. Even if parts of it are bitten off by fish Pokémon, it will return to normal within a few hours.

forms.name: Gastrodon
forms.entry: Found more often on the land than in the sea. More active when it’s cloudy or rainy out than when the weather is fair.

forms.name: Ambipom
forms.entry: Split into two, the tails are so adept at handling and doing things, Ambipom rarely uses its hands.

forms.name: Drifloon
forms.entry: It tugs on the hands of children to steal them away. However, it gets pulled around instead.

forms.name: Drifblim
forms.entry: It carries people and Pokémon when it flies. But since it only drifts, it can end up anywhere.

forms.name: Buneary
forms.entry: It slams foes by sharply uncoiling its rolled ears. It stings enough to make a grown-up cry in pain.

forms.name: Lopunny
forms.entry: An extremely cautious Pokémon. It cloaks its body with its fluffy ear fur when it senses danger.

forms.name: Mismagius
forms.entry: Its cry sounds like an incantation. It is said the cry may rarely be imbued with happiness-giving power.

forms.name: Honchkrow
forms.entry: Becoming active at night, it is known to swarm with numerous Murkrow in tow.

forms.name: Glameow
forms.entry: It claws if displeased and purrs when affectionate. Its fickleness is very popular among some.

forms.name: Purugly
forms.entry: It is a brazen brute that barges its way into another Pokémon's nest and claims it as its own.

forms.name: Chingling
forms.entry: It emits cries by agitating an orb at the back of its throat. It moves with flouncing hops.

forms.name: Stunky
forms.entry: It protects itself by spraying a noxious fluid from its rear. The stench lingers for 24 hours.

forms.name: Skuntank
forms.entry: It sprays a vile-smelling fluid from the tip of its tail to attack. Its range is over 160 feet.

forms.name: Bronzor
forms.entry: There are researchers who believe this Pokémon reflected like a mirror in the distant past.

forms.name: Bronzong
forms.entry: It brought rains by opening portals to another world. It was revered as a bringer of plentiful harvests.

forms.name: Bonsly
forms.entry: It looks as if it is always crying. It is actually adjusting its body's fluid levels by eliminating excess.

forms.name: Mime Jr.
forms.entry: It habitually mimics foes. Once mimicked, the foe cannot take its eyes off this Pokémon.

forms.name: Happiny
forms.entry: It loves round white things. It carries an egg-shaped rock in imitation of Chansey.

forms.name: Chatot
forms.entry: It can learn and speak human words. If they gather, they all learn the same saying.

forms.name: Spiritomb
forms.entry: A Pokémon that was formed by 108 spirits. It is bound to a fissure in an odd keystone.

forms.name: Gible
forms.entry: It nests in small, horizontal holes in cave walls. It pounces to catch prey that stray too close.

forms.name: Gabite
forms.entry: There is a long-held belief that medicine made from its scales will heal even incurable illnesses.

forms.name: Garchomp
forms.entry: When it folds up its body and extends its wings, it looks like a jet plane. It flies at sonic speed.

forms.name: Munchlax
forms.entry: It wolfs down its weight in food once a day, swallowing food whole with almost no chewing.

forms.name: Riolu
forms.entry: The aura that emanates from its body intensifies to alert others if it is afraid or sad.

forms.name: Lucario
forms.entry: By catching the aura emanating from others, it can read their thoughts and movements.

forms.name: Hippopotas
forms.entry: It lives in arid places. Instead of perspiration, it expels grainy sand from its body.

forms.name: Hippowdon
forms.entry: It brandishes its gaping mouth in a display of fearsome strength. It raises vast quantities of sand while attacking.

forms.name: Skorupi
forms.entry: As soon as the tail claws close, its needle tips secrete poison. It can survive a year without food.

forms.name: Drapion
forms.entry: Its body is encased in a sturdy shell. Its head rotates 180 degrees, eliminating blind spots.

forms.name: Croagunk
forms.entry: Its cheeks hold poison sacs. It tries to catch foes off guard to jab them with toxic fingers.

forms.name: Toxicroak
forms.entry: It has a poison sac at its throat. When it croaks, the stored poison is churned for greater potency.

forms.name: Carnivine
forms.entry: It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling saliva, then chomps down. It takes a whole day to eat prey.

forms.name: Finneon
forms.entry: After long exposure to sunlight, the patterns on its tail fins shine vividly when darkness arrives.

forms.name: Lumineon
forms.entry: It lives on the deep-sea floor. It attracts prey by flashing the patterns on its four tail fins.

forms.name: Mantyke
forms.entry: A friendly Pokémon that captures the subtle flows of seawater using its two antennae.

forms.name: Snover
forms.entry: It lives on snowy mountains. Having had little contact with humans, it is boldly inquisitive.

forms.name: Abomasnow
forms.entry: If it sees any packs of Darumaka going after Snover, it chases them off, swinging its sizable arms like hammers.

forms.name: Weavile
forms.entry: Evolution made it even more devious. It communicates by clawing signs in boulders.

forms.name: Magnezone
forms.entry: Sometimes the magnetism emitted by Magnezone is too strong, making them attract each other so they cannot move.

forms.name: Lickilicky
forms.entry: The long tongue is always soggy with slobber. The saliva contains a solvent that causes numbness.

forms.name: Rhyperior
forms.entry: From holes in its palms, it fires out Geodude. Its carapace can withstand volcanic eruptions.

forms.name: Tangrowth
forms.entry: It ensnares prey by extending arms made of vines. Losing arms to predators does not trouble it.

forms.name: Electivire
forms.entry: It pushes the tips of its two tails against the foe, then lets loose with over 20,000 volts of power.

forms.name: Magmortar
forms.entry: Magmortar takes down its enemies by shooting fireballs, which burn them to a blackened crisp. It avoids this method when hunting prey.

forms.name: Togekiss
forms.entry: It will never appear where there is strife. Its sightings have become rare recently.

forms.name: Yanmega
forms.entry: This six-legged Pokémon is easily capable of transporting an adult in flight. The wings on its tail help it stay balanced.

forms.name: Leafeon
forms.entry: Just like a plant, it uses photosynthesis. As a result, it is always enveloped in clear air.

forms.name: Glaceon
forms.entry: As a protective technique, it can completely freeze its fur to make its hairs stand like needles.

forms.name: Gliscor
forms.entry: If it succeeds in catching even a faint breeze properly, it can circle the globe without flapping once.

forms.name: Mamoswine
forms.entry: A frozen one was dug up from soil dating back 10,000 years. It woke up to much amazement.

forms.name: Porygon-Z
forms.entry: Its programming was modified to enable it to travel through alien dimensions. Seems there might have been an error...

forms.name: Gallade
forms.entry: A master of courtesy and swordsmanship, it fights using extending swords on its elbows.

forms.name: Probopass
forms.entry: It exudes strong magnetism from all over. It controls three small units called Mini-Noses.

forms.name: Dusknoir
forms.entry: The antenna on its head captures radio waves from the world of spirits that command it to take people there.

forms.name: Froslass
forms.entry: Legends in snowy regions say that a woman who was lost on an icy mountain was reborn as Froslass.

forms.name: Rotom
forms.entry: Its body is composed of plasma. It is known to infiltrate electronic devices and wreak havoc.

forms.name: Rotom
forms.entry: This Rotom has possessed a convection microwave oven that uses a special motor. It also has a flair for manipulating flames.

forms.name: Rotom
forms.entry: This form of Rotom enjoys coming up with water-based pranks. Be careful with it if you don't want your room flooded.

forms.name: Rotom
forms.entry: Rotom assumes this form when it takes over a refrigerator powered by a special motor. It battles by spewing cold air.

forms.name: Rotom
forms.entry: In this form, Rotom applies its new power over wind to its love of pranks. It will happily blow away any important documents it can find.

forms.name: Rotom
forms.entry: This is Rotom after it's seized control of a lawn mower that has a special motor. As it mows down grass, it scatters the clippings everywhere.

forms.name: Uxie
forms.entry: Known as "The Being of Knowledge." It is said that it can wipe out the memory of those who see its eyes.

forms.name: Mesprit
forms.entry: Known as "The Being of Emotion." It taught humans the nobility of sorrow, pain, and joy.

forms.name: Azelf
forms.entry: Known as "The Being of Willpower." It sleeps at the bottom of a lake to keep the world in balance.

forms.name: Dialga
forms.entry: It has the power to control time. It appears in Sinnoh-region myths as an ancient deity.

forms.name: Dialga
forms.entry: Radiant light caused Dialga to take on a form bearing a striking resemblance to the creator Pokémon. Dialga now wields such colossal strength that one must conclude this is its true form.

forms.name: Palkia
forms.entry: It has the ability to distort space. It is described as a deity in Sinnoh-region mythology.

forms.name: Palkia
forms.entry: It soars across the sky in a form that greatly resembles the creator of all things. Perhaps this imitation of appearance is Palkia's strategy for gaining Arceus's powers.

forms.name: Heatran
forms.entry: It dwells in volcanic caves. It digs in with its cross-shaped feet to crawl on ceilings and walls.

forms.name: Regigigas
forms.entry: It's said that Regigigas created other Pokémon from many different materials before it moved the continents to where they are today.

forms.name: Giratina
forms.entry: A Pokémon that is said to live in a world on the reverse side of ours. It appears in an ancient cemetery.

forms.name: Giratina
forms.entry: Giratina loses its legs upon changing into this form. It is believed this Pokémon must hail from a world where the heavens and the earth are as one, though there is no way of proving it.

forms.name: Cresselia
forms.entry: On nights around the quarter moon, the aurora from its tail extends and undulates beautifully.

forms.name: Phione
forms.entry: A Pokémon that lives in warm seas. It inflates the flotation sac on its head to drift and search for food.

forms.name: Manaphy
forms.entry: Born on a cold seafloor, it will swim great distances to return to its birthplace.

forms.name: Darkrai
forms.entry: Folklore has it that on moonless nights, this Pokémon will make people see horrific nightmares.

forms.name: Shaymin
forms.entry: It lives in flower patches and avoids detection by curling up to look like a flowering plant.

forms.name: Shaymin
forms.entry: Upon taking in the scent of a particular rare flower, Shaymin is enveloped in light, and its tiny body transforms.

forms.name: Arceus
forms.entry: It is said to have emerged from an egg in a place where there was nothing, then shaped the world.
